                           <locus target="#00" n="#">Fol. 159vc: Ownership note.</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 159vc: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘብሔረ፡ ስንቃጣ፡ ዘእግዝእት[ነ]፡ማርያም፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ወእስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን። ለይኩን ለይኩን፡፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 159vc: This book is of the country of Sənqaṭa of Our Lady Mary. The one who stole it or took it by force or erased it will be excommunicated by the Authority of Peter and Paul, forever and ever, Amen and Amen. So be it, so be it.</q>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Writing exercises in the margins: fols. 2r, 2v, 5r, 11rc, 17r, 58r, 59r, 60r, 119r, &#xD;
- Interlineal correction: fols. 10vc, 11rb, 43vc, 69ra, 72rc, &#xD;
- Compressed script: fols. 11rc, 130vc.&#xD;
- A marginal note mentioning Maryam Sǝnqaṭa as the owner of the Ms.: fol. 156v.&#xD;
- Portion of the text written in compressed script: fols. 158vc-159rb.&#xD;
- The ownership note is rewritten by pen immediately below the original: fol. 159vc.</item>
